#Explanation


- Sorting using Bubble sort

Explanation:

In the selection sort algorithm, initially, it compares  the first element with the current  element and after that it swaps the value if smaller than tha first element.

Test Cases:

1. Check if we are inserting any value or not.
2. Check array should not be sorted

Example

Input: [4, 1, 3, 9, 7]

Output: [1, 3, 4, 7, 9 ]


#Explanation END



package vaibhav;

public class Strings {
	
	public static void bubble(int arr[]){
		int n = arr.length;
		for(int i=0; i<=n-2;i++) {
			
			for(int j=0; j<=n-2-i; j++) {
				if(arr[j] > arr[j+1]) {
					int temp = arr[j];
					arr[j] = arr[j+1];
					arr[j+1] = temp;
			
				}
			}
			System.out.println(swap);
		}
		
	}
	
	public static void print(int arr[]) {
		for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++) {
			System.out.print(arr[i]+" ");
		}
		System.out.println();
	}

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		int arr[] = {4, 1, 3, 9, 7};
		if(arr.length<=1)
		{
			System.out.print("invalid input");
			}
		else {
			
		
		bubble(arr);
		print(arr);
		}
	}

}
